  <h2 id="early-life">Early life</h2>
  <p>
    50 Cent grew up in South Jamaica, Queens, a tough neighborhood with a
    lot of gang activity<sup><a href="#ref4">[4]</a></sup>. His mother died
    when he was a child, and he was raised mostly by his
    grandmother<sup><a href="#ref4">[4]</a></sup>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="career">Career</h2>
  <p>
    50 Cent started making music in 1996. In 2000, he was shot nine times
    and survived, an event that became a big part of his
    story<sup><a href="#ref2">[2]</a></sup>. In 2002, rapper Eminem
    discovered him and signed him to Shady Records<sup><a href="#ref2">[2]</a></sup>.
    His first major album, <em>Get Rich or Die Tryin'</em>, was released in
    2003 and became very successful<sup><a href="#ref5">[5]</a></sup>.
  </p>
  <p>
    He also formed a rap group called G-Unit with fellow rappers Lloyd Banks
    and Tony Yayo<sup><a href="#ref1">[1]</a></sup>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="business">Business ventures</h2>
  <p>
    Outside of music, 50 Cent has worked as an actor and television
    producer<sup><a href="#ref5">[5]</a></sup>. He has also invested in
    different companies and started his own record label, G-Unit
    Records<sup><a href="#ref1">[1]</a></sup>.
  </p>

